ANTHRAX - INDIA (04): (ODISHA, SIMILIPAL NATIONAL PARK) ELEPHANT CALF
*********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 1 Sep 2020
Source: Sambad English Bureau [edited]
https://sambadenglish.com/elephant-calf-dies-of-anthrax-in-odishas-similipal/


An elephant calf died of anthrax disease in Similipal National Park of Mayurbhanj district. As per reports, initially, locals spotted the carcass of the elephant calf near Rajapal village under Jamuani section in Similipal today [1 Sep 2020].

After being informed, Forest personnel reached the spot and recovered the carcass of the elephant calf.

The age of the elephant calf was in between 2 to 3 years. Following post mortem, it was known that the baby elephant died of anthrax, said a Forest official. Later the Forest personnel buried the body of the baby elephant.

--
