[Maps of India: http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7739927,60923.
Similipal National Park is on the NE border of Odisha State; for a description and map go to https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simlipal_National_Park.

Some recent ProMED reports of elephant deaths from anthrax in Similipal are:
Anthrax - India: (OR) elephant calf, susp 20190108.6248359
Anthrax - India (16): (OR) elephant, susp 20171019.5391252
Anthrax - India (15): (OR) elephants, return investigation 20171010.5371468
Anthrax - India (05): (OR) elephant 20170403.4944438
Anthrax - India (28): (OR) elephant calf 20161017.4565444
Anthrax - India (26): (OR) elephant, investigation 20160922.4508257
Anthrax - India (25): (OR) elephant, confirmed 20160915.4490919

Frankly, anthrax is rare in juvenile animals of whatever species, other than _Homo sapiens_ who get exposed when helping a relative slaughter and butcher a sick infected animal. But for livestock and wildlife, the usual juvenile problem is starvation when their mother dies of the disease. In Odisha, the veterinary services, livestock and wildlife, are very experienced with this disease so I do not doubt their diagnosis. But I do wonder how this elephant got infected and whether there might be other carcasses yet to be discovered. - Mod.MHJ]
